                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3" class="headerSilver">About Defiant</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3"><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">Defiant 
                        is a raid intensive and PvP active guild. We focus primarily 
                        on new content for raid purposes. This means the time 
                        we spend online is usually allocated to raiding and/or 
                        PvP. Raiding is not the entire focus with our guild. PvP 
                        is an equally important aspect of our daily operations. 
                        Defiant prides itself on having strong group - and mass 
                        - PvP experience and it is this style of PvP that enables 
                        us - among other things - to meet our PvE goals. 
                        <p><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">Defiant 
                          is primarily an EST-PST based guild. However, we do 
                          have members from all around the globe. Our raid times 
                          are normally from 8:00 PM EST until whenever it takes 
                          to finish the encounter for the evening. Raid times 
                          may vary depending on numbers and class availability 
                          we do however raid daily.</p>
                        <p><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">Defiant 
                          is currently in the process of implementing a Raid Point 
                          loot system. Points will be awarded to members and applicants 
                          for attending events set forth by raid leaders and officers. 
                          For more information on our RP system, its rules, and 
                          how they apply to you, you can visit our RPS site at 
                          <a href="http://www.defiantrps.tk" target="_blank">http://www.defiantrps.tk</a>. 
                          <span class="XXSm">(<font color="#FF0033">Please do 
                          not attempt to register</font>, as we do not create 
                          accounts for anyone other than our members.)</span></p>
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3" class="headerSilver">About You</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3"><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">You 
                        should be an exceptional team player that shares our goals. 
                        You should be capable and willing to make yourself available 
                        to attend our activities. You should have a thorough understanding 
                        of your class in all situations, especially raids. If 
                        you do not, you should be prepared to follow directions, 
                        ask questions, and take criticism for your mistakes. You 
                        should embrace the PvP aspect of the game as much as the 
                        PvE. </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3" class="headerSilver">What to Expect</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3"><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">Once 
                        you have posted your application in the public forum it 
                        will be moved to a private forum accessible by the members 
                        of Defiant. We will watch your application for feedback 
                        from members and decide accordingly if you will be given 
                        an invite to our app guild Midnight Haven. 
                        <p><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">Once 
                          accepted into Midnight Haven you will be an applicant 
                          for two months, starting from the date we begin reviewing 
                          your application. This gives us a chance to get to know 
                          you, and evaluate you as a player and person.</p>
                        <p><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">During 
                          this two months period your attendance will be monitored. 
                          We do not have a set percentage of attendance that you 
                          must maintain, however your activeness will be a major 
                          part of the consideration for your membership. We are 
                          typically not looking for casual players. In general 
                          we need people who are eager and motivated to log in 
                          at least 4-5 days per week. Your performance during 
                          raids and PvP activities will also be taken into consideration.</p>
                        <p><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">As 
                          your two month period draws close to an end, guild members 
                          will be reminded to post any comments good or bad they 
                          may have about you in the same private forum your application 
                          was first posted. Officers do, and will, use this as 
                          a tool when making the final decision of your acceptance. 
                          However, officers reserve the final decision of weather 
                          or not any applicant is accepted into the guild.</p>
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3" class="headerSilver">Probation</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3"><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">After 
                        you are accepted into Defiant. You will be placed on a 
                        3 months probation period. This is to ensure as an applicant 
                        you did not pull the wool over our eyes. In other words, 
                        once you are accepted into Defiant, we expect that you 
                        play with the same intensity that gained our approval 
                        to make you a member. If you fail to maintain the reputation 
                        and impression you made for yourself during your trial 
                        period, you can and may be removed from Defiant. </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3" class="headerSilver">Final Comments</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr> 
                      <td colspan="3"><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">We 
                        understand that recruitment is an important part of guild 
                        stability and we are always looking for talented, productive 
                        people to join our ranks. However, we are not looking 
                        for casual players. 
                        <p><img src="layout_img/spacer.gif" width="10" height="10" align="texttop">Our 
                          application process regards new applicants as prospects 
                          that can and may be denied after the trial period ends 
                          UNLESS they have proven their worth. Just applying and 
                          meeting the requirements will NOT guarantee you will 
                          be accepted. You have to be willing and ready to earn 
                          it. So please, be honest with yourself and us during 
                          your application period. Inability to do so will most 
                          likely result in removal from Midnight Haven, or if 
                          necessary Defiant.</p>
                      </td>
                    </tr>
